features.name: MerR_1 MerR HTH family regulatory protein

HMA,Pyr_redox_2,Pyr_redox_dim Resistance to Hg(2 ) in bacteria appears to be governed by a specialized system which includes mercuric reductase. MerA protein is responsible for volatilizing mercury as Hg(0)
HMA Mercury scavenger that specifically binds to one mercury ion and which passes it to the mercuric reductase (MerA) via the MerT protein
RNase_T DNA polymerase III, epsilon subunit and related 3'-5'

Ter Trans-acting protein required for termination of DNA replication. Binds to DNA replication terminator sequences (terA to terF) to prevent the passage of replication forks. The termination efficiency will be affected by the affinity of this protein for the terminator sequence
KfrA_N Plasmid replication region DNA-binding N-term
TraF F plasmid transfer operon protein
TraH Conjugative relaxosome accessory transposon protein
Histone_HNS Belongs to the histone-like protein H-NS family
PDDEXK_1 Belongs to the helicase family. UvrD subfamily
Bac_DNA_binding Histone-like DNA-binding protein which is capable of wrapping DNA to stabilize it, and thus to prevent its denaturation under extreme environmental conditions
